Terrorists suspected to be members of Boko Haram and the Islamic State of West African Province (ISWAP) have killed dozens of persons in a club in Yobe State. The attackers, it was gathered, invaded a nightclub in Geidam, the headquarters of Geidam local government area on Wednesday night. It was gathered that the terrorists sneaked into the town and invaded the local club where they sell alcohol and dog meat. In a deliberate effort to avoid attracting the attention of the military, the terrorists tied their victims and slaughtered them with sharp knives. Findings by the Nigerian Tribune also revealed that some of the victims had their heads mutilated and placed on their bodies.   YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE ‘Officials initially offered to help but when the number of able-bodied citizens at the centre increased, they left us unattended to’
